Preheat your #oven to 200°C. Halve, peel and thinly slice the @red onion{1}. Halve the @bell pepper{2} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(grated with garlic press). Trim and thinly slice the @spring onion{2}. Cut the @lime{1/2} into wedges. Drain and rinse the @mixed beans{1%can} in a #sieve.

Pop the peppers onto a #baking tray{}, drizzle with @oil{} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to coat then spread out in a single layer. Roast on the middle shelf of your #oven until golden and soft, ~{15-17%mins}.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #saucepan{} over medium-high heat. Once hot, add the red onion and @diced chicken breast{260%g}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until soft, ~{4-5%mins}. IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling chicken and its packaging. Add the garlic, @chipotle paste{20%g}, @smoked paprika{1%tsp} and @tomato puree{30%g} and cook, stirring, for ~{1%minute}. TIP: Add less chipotle paste if you don't like spice. Add the @finely chopped tomatoes{1%can} with the @vegetable stock paste{10%g} and a splash of water. Season with salt and pepper, and a pinch of @sugar{}. Stir in the mixed beans. Lower the heat and simmer until thickened, ~{8-10%mins}. Stir occasionally. IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

While the stew cooks, make the tortilla chips - using some clean #scissors{}, cut each @super soft tortillas with whole wheat{2} into eight triangles. Place the chips on a baking tray and drizzle over some @oil{}. Season with salt and pepper, then spread them out in a single layer. Bake on the top shelf of your #oven until golden, ~{4-5%mins}. TIP: Keep an eye on them to make sure they don't burn.

Once the peppers are roasted, add them to the stew and stir them through. Add a splash of water to loosen if you need to. Taste and season with salt and pepper. Crumble the @feta cheese{50%g} into small pieces.

Divide the stew between #bowls{} and top with the feta and sliced spring onion. Serve with lime wedges for squeezing over and tortilla chips alongside for dipping. Enjoy!